<p>That is not true, but I like the confident way Gemini said it.  </p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3.jpg" alt="" width="840" height="716" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3.jpg 1216w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3-300x256.jpg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3-1024x873.jpg 1024w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/ewp-3-768x655.jpg 768w"></a></p>
<p>The character’s name is correct, though, so it’s not able to do the complicated task of saying who played a character?</p>
<p>So there you go.  As with all things LLM, it’s wonky and really unreliable, but it’s kinda sorta useful, anyway.</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4.jpeg" alt="" width="840" height="504" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4.jpeg 2497w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4-300x180.jpeg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4-1024x616.jpeg 1024w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4-768x462.jpeg 768w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4-1536x923.jpeg 1536w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-4-2048x1231.jpeg 2048w"></a></p>
<p>And how much is this all costing me?  I’ve done 18 queries, and it’s $0.05?  Well, that’s pretty cheap.</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdZSDLlfJPGDSC03532.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdZSDLlfJPGDSC03532.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdZSDLlfJPGDSC03532.jpg 800w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdZSDLlfJPGDSC03532-300x200.jpg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdZSDLlfJPGDSC03532-768x512.jpg 768w"></a></p>
<p>Now I just have to tie it all together, and I’m all set.  Er…  which keys on this “tv remote” that I’m using is free?  Hm…</p>
<p>No, they’re all taken…  OK, Fn + Mute should work.</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wddPxyLxJPGDSC03533.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wddPxyLxJPGDSC03533.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wddPxyLxJPGDSC03533.jpg 800w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wddPxyLxJPGDSC03533-300x200.jpg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wddPxyLxJPGDSC03533-768x512.jpg 768w"></a></p>
<p>Tada!  OK, I should probably Prompt Engineer<img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2122.png" alt="™"> a bit to get the verbosity down, or do some filtering or something, but whatevs.  And the information is wrong (right character, wrong actor), but you can’t have everything.</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdSuYu5FJPGDSC03534.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdSuYu5FJPGDSC03534.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdSuYu5FJPGDSC03534.jpg 800w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdSuYu5FJPGDSC03534-300x200.jpg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdSuYu5FJPGDSC03534-768x512.jpg 768w"></a></p>
<p>No, that’s Christine Baranski!!!  But what if I try o4-mini instead of gpt-4.1-mini?</p>
<pre>"That “mystery lady” isn’t Cybill Shepherd at all but a one‐off patient named Mrs. Bagwell, who turns up in Season 2, Episode 16 (“Plugged In”).  The part of Mrs. Bagwell was played by character actress Gretchen Wyler.  Wyler was already well known on Broadway and in soap operas when she popped up in Cybill’s hospital storyline for that single episode. "</pre>
<p>That’s even wronger!  And it took half a minute to complete, which makes it less fun to use.</p>
<p>Oh, well.</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdCdycJbJPGDSC03540.jpg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdCdycJbJPGDSC03540.jpg" alt="" width="800" height="533" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdCdycJbJPGDSC03540.jpg 800w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdCdycJbJPGDSC03540-300x200.jpg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/wdCdycJbJPGDSC03540-768x512.jpg 768w"></a></p>
<p>What about a reality show?  Well, all of that is wrong, but they are indeed in Australia…</p>
<p>Anyway.   Presumably all TVs have this sort of thing built in now?  A “who’s that, then?” button?  I have no idea — I only watch physical media (via <a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/2025/07/26/battle-ground-raid/">Emacs</a>).  But now Emacs has this functionality, too, and that’s surely the most important thing.  (Code on <a href="https://github.com/larsmagne/movie.el">Microsoft Github</a> as usual.)</p>
<p>Edit the day after: I apparently was looking at the source of a 2018 version of mpv I had here.  Newer versions have this command:</p>
<p><a href="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15.jpeg"><img loading="lazy" src="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15.jpeg" alt="" width="840" height="313" srcset="https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15.jpeg 1277w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15-300x112.jpeg 300w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15-1024x382.jpeg 1024w, https://lars.ingebrigtsen.no/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/2025-09-21-15-768x286.jpeg 768w"></a></p>
